# Git Commit / Push Policy

**Never run `git commit` or `git push` without explicit confirmation from the user.**

## Required flow

1. Show the user a summary of what will be committed (files changed, brief description of changes).
2. Ask: "Shall I commit and push this?" — or wait for the user to say "commit", "push", "yes go ahead", etc.
3. Only then run `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push`.

## What counts as explicit confirmation

- "commit and push"
- "yes", "go ahead", "do it", "push it"
- "lets push", "push"
- The user triggering a plan → agent mode transition and saying implement

## What does NOT count

- Completing a set of code changes (even if all todos are done)
- The user saying "done" or "looks good" about the code itself
- A build passing cleanly

## Never do this automatically

Do not commit as part of implementing a plan unless the user has specifically asked for it in that message.
